Click here

7. REMOVE REAR LIGHT ASSEMBLY LH

Click here

8. REMOVE REAR LIGHT ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

9. REMOVE NO. 3 LUGGAGE ROOM WIRE

(a) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Disengage the 7 clamps and remove the No. 3 luggage room wire.

(b) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Disengage the 12 clamps and remove the No. 3 luggage room wire.

10. REMOVE LOWER REAR BUMPER COVER

(a) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Hook

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the hook to remove the lower rear bumper cover.

11. REMOVE CENTER REAR BUMPER GUARD (for Type A)

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the 14 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the center rear bumper guard.

Remove in this Direction

12. REMOVE CENTER REAR BUMPER GUARD (for Type B)

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Remove the 2 clips.

(c) Disengage the 16 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the center rear bumper guard.

Remove in this Direction

-

-

13. REMOVE REAR BUMPER EXTENSION FILLER LH (for Type A)

(a) Remove the 2 clips.

(b) Disengage the 3 claws and 2 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the rear bumper extension filler LH.

Remove in this Direction

14. REMOVE REAR BUMPER EXTENSION FILLER LH (for Type B)

(a) Remove the 2 clips.

(b) Disengage the 3 claws and 2 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the rear bumper extension filler LH.

Remove in this Direction

15. REMOVE REAR BUMPER EXTENSION FILLER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

16. REMOVE NO. 1 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 1 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

17. REMOVE NO. 2 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 2 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

18. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SEAL

(a) Remove the rear bumper arm seal.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

19. REMOVE NO. 3 REAR BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 3 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

20. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER LH

(a) Disengage the 3 clips as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the guide as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction (1)

Remove in this Direction (2)

(c) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration to remove the rear bumper side retainer LH.

21. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

22. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL LH

(a) Remove the rear bumper side clip.

*1

Rear Bumper Side Clip

(b) Remove the 3 clips and rear bumper side seal LH.

23. REMOVE REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

24. REMOVE NO. 1 REAR BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Remove the 6 bolts and No. 1 rear bumper reinforcement.

25. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and rear bumper arm sub-assembly LH.

26. REMOVE REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.
